# Architecture

## Monorepo layout

- **apps/** — Deployable applications.
  - **apps/api** — Express backend serving all future apps (task manager, meal planner, etc.).
  - **apps/web** — React frontend: home screen, login, and navigation to other apps.
  - Future apps (e.g. task-manager, meal-planner) will live under `apps/` as separate workspaces.
- **packages/** — Shared libraries; no standalone deployment.
  - **packages/db** — Prisma schema, migrations, generated client, and single `prisma` export.
  - Other shared packages (e.g. types, shared utils) will live under `packages/` as needed.

## Package and app responsibilities

| Location        | Responsibility |
|----------------|----------------|
| **packages/db** | Prisma schema, migrations, generated client output, single PrismaClient instance. Source of truth for database shape and connection. |
| **apps/api**    | Express server, session, auth, and API routes for all apps. No direct Prisma instantiation; uses `@home-lab/db`. |
| **apps/web**    | React app: home screen, login, and navigation to other apps. Consumes API and shared types. |
| **Future apps** | Each under `apps/`; may depend on `@home-lab/db` and shared packages; no app-to-app dependencies. |

## Dependency rules

- Apps **may** depend on packages (e.g. `apps/api` depends on `@home-lab/db`).
- Packages **must not** depend on apps.
- Apps **must not** depend on other apps; shared behaviour goes into packages.
- Workspace packages are referenced by name (e.g. `@home-lab/db`) with `workspace:*` in package.json.

## Prisma generation and consumption

- Prisma client is generated **into** `packages/db/src/generated/prisma` (see generator `output` in schema).
- **Consume only via** the db package: `import { prisma } from "@home-lab/db"`. Do not import from `packages/db/src/generated/prisma` from outside the db package.
- Re-export types from `@home-lab/db` as needed so apps and other packages use a single entry point.

## Environment variables

- **packages/db**: Loads `packages/db/.env` for `DATABASE_URL` (and any Prisma/Neon-specific vars). Used when running migrations or when the db package initialises the client.
- **apps/api**, **apps/web**, and other apps: May each have their own `.env` (e.g. `PORT`, `SESSION_SECRET`, API base URL). App env is the source of truth for that app.
- Root `.env` is optional; prefer package- or app-level `.env` so each boundary has clear ownership.

## Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph apps [Apps]
    api[apps/api]
    web[apps/web]
    future[Future apps]
  end
  subgraph packages [Packages]
    db[packages/db]
    shared[Future shared]
  end
  api --> db
  web --> shared
  api --> shared
  future --> db
  future --> shared
```
